First, let's find the symmetric difference of A and B (A ⊕ B). The symmetric difference of two sets is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection.

A = {1, 2}
B = {2, 3}

Intersection of A and B: A ∩ B = {2}

A ⊕ B = {1, 3} (elements in either A or B, but not in their intersection)

Now, let's find the symmetric difference of (A ⊕ B) and {1}:

(A ⊕ B) = {1, 3}
{1}

Intersection of (A ⊕ B) and {1}: (A ⊕ B) ∩ {1} = {1}

(A ⊕ B) ⊕ {1} = {3} (elements in either (A ⊕ B) or {1}, but not in their intersection)

Finally, let's find the Cartesian product of ((A ⊕ B) ⊕ {1}) and B:

((A ⊕ B) ⊕ {1}) = {3}
B = {2, 3}

((A ⊕ B) ⊕ {1}) × B = {(3, 2), (3, 3)}
